ng your IDE."},"113":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-5","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"Go to Cursor Settings → Features → MCP Servers."},"114":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-6","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"Click Add New MCP Server and enter:"},"115":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"Name: ambriel"},"116":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"Type: url"},"117":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"URL: https://mcp.ambriel.io/compliance"},"118":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"After adding the server, Cursor will prompt you to authorize the connection. A browser window will open — log in with your Ambriel credentials and approve the access request."},"119":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-11","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"The Ambriel tools are now available to Cursor's AI. Try asking:"},"120":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-12","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"\"Check if this email is risky\""},"121":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-13","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"\"Screen this company for PEP status\""},"122":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-14","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"\"Look up this phone number\""},"123":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor-15","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/cursor#setup","content":"Cursor's AI will automatically use the MCP tools when relevant to your code. For example, if you're reviewing a user registration flow, it can check the email and phone in real time."},"124":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"page","content":"AI Agents & MCP","url":"/docs/ui/agents"},"125":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-0","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents","content":"Connect Ambriel to Claude, ChatGPT, Cursor, Windsurf and other AI agents via MCP (Model Context Protocol)"},"126":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-1","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/agents#what-is-mcp","content":"What is MCP?"},"127":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-2","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/agents#authentication","content":"Authentication"},"128":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-3","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/agents#available-agents","content":"Available Agents"},"129":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-4","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/agents#quick-start","content":"Quick Start"},"130":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-5","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents","content":"Ambriel provides a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that lets AI agents and coding assistants interact with the Ambriel API directly. This means you can query fraud scores, screen entities, check email/phone/IP reputation, and perform KYB evaluations — all from within your AI tool."},"131":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-6","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#what-is-mcp","content":"The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard that connects AI models with external tools and data sources. Ambriel's MCP server acts as a bridge, giving your AI agent access to the full Ambriel API surface."},"132":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#authentication","content":"Ambriel's MCP server uses OAuth for authentication. When you first connect, your AI agent will open a browser window prompting you to log in with your Ambriel credentials and authorize access. No manual API key management is needed."},"133":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#quick-start","content":"All agents connect to Ambriel using the same MCP server URL. No API key is required — OAuth handles authentication automatically."},"134":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#quick-start","content":"When you add the MCP server, your AI agent will open a browser to authorize with Ambriel. Accept the prompt, and the connection is established. Your session is persisted for subsequent uses."},"135":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents#quick-start","content":"Select your agent above for platform-specific setup instructions."},"136":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"page","content":"Windsurf","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf"},"137":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-0","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","content":"Connect Ambriel to Windsurf AI editor via MCP"},"138":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-1","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#windsurf","content":"Windsurf"},"139":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-2","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#setup","content":"Setup"},"140":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-3","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#example","content":"Example"},"141":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-4","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#windsurf","content":"Connect Ambriel to Windsurf, the AI-powered IDE, enabling fraud checks and entity screening directly in your development workflow."},"142":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-5","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#setup","content":"Windsurf uses a global MCP configuration file. Create or edit the file at:"},"143":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-6","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#setup","content":"macOS / Linux: ~/.codeium/windsurf/mcp_config.json"},"144":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#setup","content":"Windows: %USERPROFILE%\\.codeium\\windsurf\\mcp_config.json"},"145":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#setup","content":"Add the following configuration with the URL format:"},"146":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#setup","content":"Restart Windsurf. When you first use an Ambriel tool, Windsurf will open a browser window for OAuth authentication. Sign in with your Ambriel credentials and authorize the connection."},"147":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#setup","content":"The Ambriel tools are now available to the Windsurf AI assistant."},"148":{"id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf-11","page_id":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/agents/windsurf#setup","content":"You can also add project-specific MCP configurations by placing a .mcp.json file in your project root. This is useful when different projects need different authorization scopes."},"149":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"page","content":"AML Compliance","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance"},"150":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-0","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","content":"Ambriel's AML compliance solutions are designed to simplify regulatory adherence while enhancing fraud detection capabilities."},"151":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-1","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#what-is-aml-compliance","content":"What is AML Compliance?"},"152":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-2","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#what-does-ambriels-aml-compliance-solution-do","content":"What does Ambriel's AML Compliance solution do?"},"153":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-3","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#screening","content":"Screening"},"154":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-4","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#monitoring","content":"Monitoring"},"155":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-5","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#data-management","content":"Data Management"},"156":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-6","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#how-does-it-work","content":"How does it work?"},"157":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#what-is-aml-compliance","content":"The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommends that countries implement effective Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and Combating the Financing of Terrorism (CFT) regulations. The European Union's 5th and 6th Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD5/6) also require screening against global sanction lists, PEP (Politically Exposed Persons) databases, and high-risk profiles."},"158":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#what-does-ambriels-aml-compliance-solution-do","content":"Ambriel's AML compliance solution is designed to help businesses detect and prevent financial crimes. It does this by providing real-time screening, monitoring, and data management capabilities."},"159":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#screening","content":"The AML API screens customers against global sanction lists, PEP databases, and high-risk profiles. This ensures that businesses are compliant with AML regulations and can detect potential fraud."},"160":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#monitoring","content":"The AML API also provides continuous monitoring, alerting businesses to any changes in a customer's compliance status over time."},"161":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-11","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#data-management","content":"The AML API provides a secure and reliable way to manage customer data, ensuring that it is up-to-date and accurate. Additionally, all searches and results are stored in a secure and tamper-proof log for 5 years, providing a complete audit trail."},"162":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance-12","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/aml-compliance#how-does-it-work","content":"The AML API integrates seamlessly with the Fraud API, providing a holistic approach to financial crime prevention. The AML API is designed to be compatible with the Anti-Money Laundering Directive (AMLD5/6) of the European Union, as well as the recommendations of the Financial Action Task Force (FATF)."},"163":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"page","content":"Entities","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities"},"164":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-0","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","content":"Understand the entities in AML context"},"165":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-1","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#what-are-entities-in-aml-context","content":"What are Entities in AML Context?"},"166":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-2","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#types-of-entities","content":"Types of Entities"},"167":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-3","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#politically-exposed-persons-pep","content":"Politically Exposed Persons (PEP)"},"168":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-4","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#sanctions-lists","content":"Sanctions Lists"},"169":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-5","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#crime-lists","content":"Crime Lists"},"170":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-6","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#watch-lists","content":"Watch Lists"},"171":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-7","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#why-are-entities-important-in-aml","content":"Why are Entities Important in AML?"},"172":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-8","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"How Can You Use Ambriel's Entities Feature?"},"173":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-9","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-to-create-an-entity","content":"How to create an Entity?"},"174":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-10","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"heading","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#entity-fields","content":"Entity Fields"},"175":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-11","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#what-are-entities-in-aml-context","content":"In the context of Anti-Money Laundering (AML), entities refer to individuals, companies, or organizations that are subject to AML regulations. These entities can be either natural persons (e.g. individuals) or legal persons (e.g. companies). Ambriel's AML solution scans over 120 sources and continuously improves to provide the most accurate and up-to-date information."},"176":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-12","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#politically-exposed-persons-pep","content":"PEPs are individuals who hold or have held prominent public offices, such as heads of state, government officials, politicians, or high-ranking military officers. PEPs are considered high-risk due to their potential exposure to corruption and bribery."},"177":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-13","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#sanctions-lists","content":"Sanctions lists are compiled by governments and international organizations to identify individuals, companies, and organizations that are subject to economic sanctions. These sanctions can be imposed due to various reasons, such as supporting terrorism, human rights violations, or nuclear proliferation."},"178":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-14","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#crime-lists","content":"Crime lists are databases of individuals and companies that have been convicted of or are suspected of committing crimes, such as fraud, money laundering, or organized crime."},"179":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-15","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#watch-lists","content":"Watch lists are databases of individuals and companies that are under surveillance by law enforcement or other authorities. These lists are used to identify and monitor potential security threats, such as terrorists, organized crime groups, or individuals with a history of fraudulent activities. Watch lists can be used to flag suspicious transactions, prevent fraud, and protect against potential security threats."},"180":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-16","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#why-are-entities-important-in-aml","content":"Entities play a crucial role in AML as they can be used to conceal illegal activities, such as money laundering and terrorist financing. Therefore, it is essential to identify and monitor entities to prevent illegal activities and ensure compliance with AML regulations."},"181":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-17","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Ambriel's Entities feature allows you to screen entities against PEP, sanctions, and crime lists in real-time. You can use this feature to:"},"182":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-18","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Verify the identity of customers and suppliers"},"183":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-19","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Check for potential AML risks"},"184":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-20","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Monitor transactions and activities"},"185":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-21","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-can-you-use-ambriels-entities-feature","content":"Comply with AML regulations"},"186":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-22","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/entities#how-to-create-an-entity","content":"Login to dashboard"},"187":{"id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities-23","page_id":"/docs/ui/aml/entities","type":"text","url":"/docs/ui/aml/e